# MCP Servers Configuration

## Playwright MCP Server
- **Added**: npx @playwright/mcp@latest
- **Purpose**: Browser automation and testing capabilities
- **Node.js**: Requires v20+ (upgraded from v18.19.1 to v20.19.4)
- **Installation**: `claude mcp add playwright "npx @playwright/mcp@latest"`

### Usage
The Playwright MCP server provides browser automation capabilities for:
- Web scraping
- UI testing
- Screenshot capture
- Browser interaction automation

### Available Options
- `--browser <browser>`: chrome, firefox, webkit, msedge
- `--headless`: Run browser in headless mode
- `--viewport-size <size>`: Set browser viewport (e.g., "1280, 720")
- `--device <device>`: Emulate device (e.g., "iPhone 15")
- `--caps <caps>`: Enable capabilities (vision, pdf)